PN,39902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1775049066
OL,3,C'No patient will be left without care'
OL,4,Cafter hospice cuts
OL,6,FThe hospice said a combination of
OL,7,Fincreasing costs, an aging population
OL,8,Fand only 24% of its funding coming
OL,9,Ffrom the Government had meant it had
OL,10,Fbeen operating at a deficit for the
OL,11,Fpast six years.
OL,13,FIt was not a position it could
OL,14,Fmaintain, it said, "without risking
OL,15,Fthe long-term future of the charity".
OL,17,FGovernment funding accounts for around
OL,18,F24% of total income at the hospice,
OL,19,Fwith the remaining amount raised
OL,20,Fthrough donations and fundraising.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,400,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F399A1775049066
OL,3,C'No patient will be left without care'
OL,4,Cafter hospice cuts
OL,6,FThe minister said that while these
OL,7,Ffigures are "arithmetically correct",
OL,8,Fcomparisons with the UK and Jersey
OL,9,F"must be treated with caution" due to
OL,10,Fdifferences in each funding model.
OL,12,FShe claimed that government funding
OL,13,Fequates to around 37% of core clinical
OL,14,Fstaffing costs, and confirmed the
OL,15,Fhospice will receive #1.8 million in
OL,16,F2026-27, up from #1.755 million in the
OL,17,Fcurrent financial year.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
